						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the same shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ (Vikramachōḷa): No date: c. 13th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is much damaged and its lower part is not available. It appears to record a gift made by the king of land in Kallāpuram <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikra[ma*]chōḻanallūr in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu, to a certain Kaṇḍan Kāvan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śivapattaṉ (Śivabhaktan).</p>						

